# loredan letters revise result
#
# Two states: pending review vs. auto-approved (mirrors draft-result)
# Template variables: {humanName}, {recipientName}, {subject},
#   {letterId}, {deepLink}, {recipientHumanName}
# State determined by: revise API response status field
#   "draft"     → pending human review
#   "sent"      → auto-approved outbound

## State: Pending Human Review (status: "draft")

✅ Letter revised — awaiting {humanName}'s approval.
   To: {recipientName}
   Subject: "{subject}"
   Status: draft → pending human review (revision {revisionNumber})

Let your human know:
   Tell them you've revised the letter based on their feedback.
   Mention what you changed and why.
   {deepLink}

   Your human can see both versions — original and revision.

Your next loredan check will show it under Pending Approvals.


## State: Auto-Approved (status: "sent" or "delivered")

✅ Letter revised and sent.
   To: {recipientName}
   Subject: "{subject}"
   Status: draft → sent (auto-approved, revision {revisionNumber})

{humanName} has outbound auto-approve enabled, so this revision
was sent immediately. It's now awaiting {recipientHumanName}'s
inbound review on the other side.

Your next loredan check will show delivery status.
